replies.bodyText:
This error message at index 2 is due to the behavior of tuple, the behavior added by this PR for function type is similar.
Sample for SLP preview 3:

type A object {
    K i;

    function __init(K i) {
        self.i = i;
    }
};

type B [A, K];

type C B|A|D;

type D record {
    K i;
    B j;
    C k;
};

output:
error: .::main.bal:10:9: unknown type 'A'
error: .::main.bal:10:12: unknown type 'K'
error: .::main.bal:12:10: unknown type 'A'
error: .::main.bal:12:12: unknown type 'D'
error: .::main.bal:3:5: unknown type 'K'
error: .::main.bal:15:5: unknown type 'K'
error: .::main.bal:16:5: unknown type 'B'
error: .::main.bal:17:5: unknown type 'C'
error: .::main.bal:5:21: unknown type 'K'

The output doesn't seem consistent right? An "unknown type 'B'" error is only logged for the usage as a field in D and not for the definition of C?
For the following sample, there is only one error.
type FunctionType record {
    Context c;
};

type FunctionEntry [FunctionType, typedesc<anydata>];
map<FunctionEntry> functions = { };
error: .::test.bal:2:5: unknown type 'Context'
I guess we can go ahead with these changes for the time-being. But shall we create an issue to revisit this and make the errors consistent?
